Having taken note of reports that SANRAL has cancelled adjudicated projects to the value of R17.4 billion, the Minister of Transport, Fikile Mbalula will join a media briefing convened by SANRAL to clarify the matter. JOHANNESBURG - The state of South Africa's roads comes into focus with the South African national roads agency giving details over the cancellation of tenders amounting to more than R17-billion. The contracts in question were meant to address issues of road maintenance and infrastructure development.